[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(2) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Their south border.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The southern boundary of Judah is thus described by Conder (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Bible Handbook, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "p. 257):—“The south boundary of Judah is described from east to west, and became afterwards that of Simeon (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 19:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Although the points mentioned along the border are not all certainly known, there is no doubt that the great mountain wall which extends from the Dead Sea to the water-shed south of Rehoboth (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Er-Ruheibeh",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") formed the natural and recognised boundary of Palestine, while the river of Egypt (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 15:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") is generally supposed to be the present ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Wâdy-el’-Arish, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the northern boundary between Syria and Egypt. The north branch of this valley ( ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Wâdy-el-Abiad",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") rises near ‘Abdeh (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Ebodah",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ")",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "south of Rehoboth, and thus carries on the boundary from the mountain rampart. A new identification of importance may be here mentioned, namely, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Hezron ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 15:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), the next point to Kadesh-barnea on the west side. Kadesh has been shown to lie probably in the neighbourhood of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Wâdy-el-Yemen, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and immediately west of that valley is the mountain called ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Hadîreh, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "a name radically identical with Hezron.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
